Things are entirely different now, than they were when I was level 35, but yes, you can definitely get by with the weapons you have now, until you reach a fairly high level.  Swiftblade of Zek, while having no proc, is a good weapon for damage (which helps aggro) and has solid stats (particularly the HP).<br>
<br>
I'd get a nice haste item, then work on acquiring +hp armors.  Most of these will have a relatively decent amount of AC on them as well.<br>
<br>
You're only level 35, so 10-20k is quite a lot of money.  You'll be able to make money faster also, when you're a bit higher level.  I'm not much up on bazaar prices, but I'm sure you can get a 26 or 30% haste item for 20kish.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Aggro:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
As Brutuz said, taunt is basically a skill check, and if it succeeds, you gain aggro on the mob (but not by a whole lot, only 1 point higher than the next highest person on the hate list).<br>
<br>
So, you are taunting multiple times before breaking a mez, and you have a chance at success each time you do it.  To the best of my knowledge, there is no cumulative effect of multiple taunts -- you're just giving yourself more chances to succeed when you do it more than once.  Until you are high level, this is certainly a good idea, because you can fail your skill check much easier than someone with maxxed skill.<br>
<br>
As for kicking/bashing vs. just swinging the weapons, well, it doesn't make much difference in the actual mez-break how you go about doing it.  When the mez is broken, you will either have aggro, or you will not.<br>
<br>
Kicking/bashing can be advantageous in that if they land, the mob will (often) be stunned, and not attacking anyone.  While your mob is in this state, for a couple of seconds, you are swinging your weapons at him, which are building hate, and also have a chance to proc, adding more hate.  All this goes on while the mob is stunned, and if... for example, the mob was still angry with your enchanter group mate when you actually broke the mez with kick, you have a few seconds to grab that aggro back and make it look like you had it all along before the stun effect wears.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>AA:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Run3 is nice for running long distances, but it's less useful for a warrior than say, a wizard, because:<br>
<br>
1).  Warriors do not solo.  If you are soloing right now, be prepared for that to change very soon.  You also don't really have cause to run away from anything, in most cases.<br>
<br>
2).  With PoK, you can get almost anywhere in the world in a few clicks of the mouse.  It's not like the old days where you had to run across zone after zone to get somewhere.<br>
<br>
For these reasons, personally, I would get to level 60 and make that a priority.  It's a huge milestone for the class, and you will be much more effective gaining AA at 60+ than you will at level 50 (I think that's the minimum you can put exp into AA at?).<br>
